==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isabella moth
<hw>Is`a*bel"la moth`</hw> <pr>(?; 115)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
common American moth (<spn>Pyrrharctia isabella</spn>), of an isabella
color. The larva, called <cref>woolly bear</cref> and <cref>hedgehog
caterpillar</cref>, is densely covered with hairs, which are black at
each end of the body, and red in the middle part.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isabelline</ent>⟦br⟧
